<div id="outline-container-headline-5" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="headline-5">
Tooltips
</h3>
<div id="outline-text-headline-5" class="outline-text-3">
<p>Emacs supports <a href="https://www.gnu.org/s/emacs/manual/html_node/emacs/Tooltips.html">tooltips</a> when the mouse hovers over when there is a pause in mouse movement over parts of text in a window, the mode line, or some other part of the Emacs frame such as a tool bar button or menu item.</p>
<p>
The layout and typography of these tooltips is in most cases controlled by the window manager. To disable this behaviour, customise the variable <code>use-system-tooltips</code> to <code>nil</code>.</p>
<p>
With this option you can finetune the appearance of the tooltip by customising `tooltip-frame-parameters` and change the font with for example: <code>(set-face-attribute &#39;tooltip nil :font &#34;Monospace-16&#34;)</code>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
